New Records: Domantas Sabonis had 23 points and a career-high 28 rebounds, becoming the first player with 20 points and 25 rebounds against the Celtics since Kareem Abdul-Jabbar in 1971
Key Match Events: Sacramento Kings opened the fourth quarter with a 24-9 run to take a 100-85 lead with 6:03 to play
Post-Match Reflections: The victory extended Sacramento's season-high win streak to six games
